1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,742
Description turns private intent into an observable brief.

2
00:00:03,692 --> 00:00:10,755
AI cannot reliably infer the audience in your head, the tradeoff you care about, or the standard you will use to reject the result.

3
00:00:10,755 --> 00:00:13,461
If those things matter, make them visible.

4
00:00:13,461 --> 00:00:23,980
A high-signal description contains five parts: the desired outcome, the relevant context, the audience or user, the hard constraints, and the evidence or test that defines success.

5
00:00:23,980 --> 00:00:28,663
Examples help when they reveal a preference, not when they merely add more text.

6
00:00:28,663 --> 00:00:31,548
Describe tradeoffs instead of adjectives.

7
00:00:31,548 --> 00:00:34,778
Make it professional” leaves many interpretations.

8
00:00:34,778 --> 00:00:43,653
Write for a skeptical engineering lead, keep the claim narrow, show the operational cost, and avoid marketing language” gives the system decisions it can act on.

9
00:00:43,653 --> 00:00:46,134
Imagine asking for a launch plan.

10
00:00:46,134 --> 00:00:49,788
A weak description says, “Create a great launch strategy.

11
00:00:49,788 --> 00:01:00,634
A useful one names the product stage, target user, available channels, budget, prohibited claims, required deliverables, and the metric that will determine whether the experiment continues.

12
00:01:00,634 --> 00:01:03,500
Description is not a one-time prompt ritual.

13
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:08,701
During collaboration, update the shared artifact and acceptance criteria as you learn.

14
00:01:08,701 --> 00:01:15,894
During delegation, package the final state so another agent or another session can resume without reconstructing the conversation.

15
00:01:15,894 --> 00:01:18,586
The common failure is context dumping.

16
00:01:18,586 --> 00:01:21,019
More context can hide the signal.

17
00:01:21,019 --> 00:01:30,230
Remove history that does not change the decision, label uncertain facts, separate requirements from suggestions, and put the most important constraint where it cannot be missed.

18
00:01:30,230 --> 00:01:35,826
First, translate intent into an outcome, context, constraints, and evidence.

19
00:01:35,826 --> 00:01:39,355
Second, describe the tradeoff the AI must preserve.

20
00:01:39,355 --> 00:01:43,627
Third, prefer a small high-signal brief over a long noisy prompt.
